BambuHelper — Python / Raspberry Pi Port
=========================================

This project is a Python port of the original BambuHelper project
for the Raspberry Pi Zero 2 W.

Original Work
-------------
Project:   BambuHelper
Author:    Keralots (https://github.com/Keralots)
Source:    https://github.com/Keralots/BambuHelper
Platform:  ESP32 / Arduino C++
Display:   ST7789 240×240 via TFT_eSPI

The following components were ported faithfully from the original C++ source:

  display_ui.cpp      → src/display.py  (screen layout, progress bar, all screen states)
  display_gauges.cpp  → src/display.py  (arc gauge drawing, 60°–300° sweep)
  display_anim.cpp    → src/display.py  (spinner, animated dots, completion ring)
  icons.h             → src/display.py  (all 16×16 and 32×32 bitmap icons)
  bambu_mqtt.cpp      → src/bambu.py    (MQTT topics, pushall, delta-merge, backoff)
  bambu_cloud.cpp     → src/cloud.py    (cloud region, JWT decode, user ID extraction)
  bambu_state.h       → src/bambu.py    (all state fields and their JSON key mappings)

Port Author
-----------
Project:   BambuHelper (Python/Pi port)
Author:    OktaneZA (https://github.com/OktaneZA)
Source:    https://github.com/OktaneZA/bambuhelper
Platform:  Raspberry Pi Zero 2 W / Python 3
Display:   Waveshare 1.54" 240×240 ST7789 LCD via Pimoroni st7789 library

Additions in this port
----------------------
- Flask web config portal (replaces ESP32 AP-mode setup)
- LAN + Cloud MQTT mode selectable via web UI
- Cloud token extractor script (scripts/get_cloud_token.py)
- Idempotent Raspberry Pi installer (install.sh)
- systemd service with watchdog and weekly reboot timer
- Post-install validator (validate.py)
- Full test suite runnable without Pi hardware (pytest, mocked GPIO/SPI)

